# Migration in-place-edit allowlist
# =================================================================
# Read by scripts/check-resupply-migration-immutability.sh.
#
# Editing (or deleting / renaming) a migration that already exists on the
# base branch is FORBIDDEN by default: migrate.mjs dedups by the sha256 of
# each file's CONTENT, so an in-place edit changes the hash and the
# deploy-time migrator re-applies the file against production — which
# fails the deploy if the rewritten SQL is not perfectly idempotent (this
# is what broke the 2026-06-05 Railway releases).
#
# The correct way to change a shipped migration's effect is a NEW,
# higher-numbered corrective migration written idempotently. Use this
# allowlist ONLY for the rare emergency where an already-applied migration
# must be made idempotent in place.
#
# Format: one migration basename per line; `#` starts a comment. Example:
#
#     0212_compliance_rules.sql  # 2026-06-05 emergency: add DROP TRIGGER IF EXISTS
#
# Remove the entry once the edit has shipped — an allowlisted file stays
# editable without a tripwire until the line is deleted.
#
# (No active entries.)
